    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Locks of various designs that are key operated or keyless letter-combination type, originating in China. When they are locked, the sliding bolt is trapped by the opening springs against the inner wall of the lock-body. They are often decorative objects as well as utilitarian.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
